5ALVtKFmD2TRh0rSusAU19k=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring vendor test interactions**\\n\\nI’m considering how the existing compendium vendor test functions, particularly regarding the source's dynamic access to vendor class. I’m not sure if tests accounted for certain variables. Native images might fail if there's no metadata for the vendor, unless the test classes exist outside a closed world. I wonder if reflective access to public constructors requires metadata, but I think it does for method calls. However, maybe using `Class.forName` needs class names created from a system property, not a constant. I'm unsure about constructor accessibility either.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking NativeImageSupport usage**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether we need to incorporate NativeImageSupport into the JVM project. It might not be necessary, but I should investigate how this class is currently being used in the tests first. Exploring its usage will give me a clearer understanding of whether it’s essential or if we can operate effectively without it. So, let’s proceed with checking those tests to make a more informed decision!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NOv8qsBYH9VJg55ApZ0p1Oce|fc_0beee1d83eb301440169f72cee8f74819ca5cd9862d79d8959", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|UnsupportedFeature\" tests/src | head -80", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1305, "output": 1819, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41524, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777806548002, "responseId": "resp_0beee1d83eb301440169f72cd47ef4819cbcd9359c8d380466"}}
